  "text": "Murine and human hematopoietic stem and progenitor cells express PGE 2 receptors PGE 2 interacts with 4 specific, highly conserved G-proteincoupled receptors: EP1-EP4, [CITATION_1] with EP receptor repertoire accounting for multiple, sometimes opposing responses attributed to PGE 2 . [CITATION_2] Although EP receptor expression has been observed in dendritic cells, [CITATION_3] monocytes, [CITATION_4] and early zebrafish hematopoietic tissue, [CITATION_5] EP receptor expression on hematopoietic stem and progenitor cell populations is not known. Analysis of EP receptors on c-kit ϩ Lin neg (KL) cells, enriched for hematopoietic progenitor cells; Sca-1 ϩ c-kit ϩ Lin neg (SKL) cells, enriched for multipotent progenitor cells as well as HSCs; and SLAM (CD150 ϩ , CD48 Ϫ ) SKL and CD34 Ϫ SKL cells, highly enriched for primitive repopulating HSCs [CITATION_6] [CITATION_7] showed that all 4 EP receptors are expressed on these hematopoietic cell populations (Figure 2A ). Analogous to murine cells, all 4 receptors are expressed on human CD34 ϩ UCB cells enriched for HSCs and CD34 ϩ , CD38 Ϫ cells that contain the most primitive human HSCs ( Figure 2B ). Quantitative RT-PCR showed that mRNA for all 4 EP receptors is detected in the whole bone marrow cell population and in FACS-sorted KL, SKL, and primitive CD34 Ϫ SKL cells ( Figure 3A ) and on common lymphoid progenitor cells (CLPs) (Lin neg , c-kit low , Sca-1 low , IL7R ϩ ) and myeloid progenitor cells (CMPs) (Lin neg , c-kit ϩ , Sca-1 Ϫ , CD34 ϩ ) (not shown). Similarly, QRT-PCR analysis detected mRNA for all 4 EP receptors in purified CD34 ϩ and CD34 ϩ , CD38 Ϫ UCB cells ( Figure 3B ).",
